  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season the chicken thighs with salt and black pepper.",
    "Heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the chicken thighs until browned on both sides, about 5 minutes per side.",
    "Transfer the chicken to a baking dish and roast in the oven for 20 minutes.",
    "While the chicken is roasting, heat the chimichurri sauce in a small saucepan over low heat.",
    "Spherify the lime juice using sodium alginate and water.",
    "Add the spherified lime juice to the chimichurri sauce and stir to combine.",
    "Add the sliced potatoes to the baking dish with the chicken and roast for an additional 10 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken and potatoes from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Slice the chicken and serve with the potatoes and spherified lime juice.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired."
  ],
